# Calendar

>* This prompt helps people create a calendar to include all of the things they must do
## Overview
This prompt produces a calendar for anything the need to do in a given timeframe

It solves the problem of time management, and staying bust while still having time to yourself

**Best For :**
- When trying to plan a summer vacation
-  When a business owner has a lot to do
-  When a student want a calendar for all their course work


**Output**
-
- A typical output looks like a calendar  with each thing you must to that time frame you give it
- ## Quick Start
### 1. Copy the prompt
Generate a calendar for [ TIME_PERIOD ] that includes [ CALENDAR_IMPUT ] [what
TIME_FOR_COMPLETION ] Make it easy to change and readable, make it in a
[FORMAT_LIKE_GOOGLE_SHEETS] with the correct formatting for that specific place.
I would like [EXCLUDED_DAYS] without anything on them, and I want to use my time
each day to its fullest potential. Make the calendar [STYLE]
### 2. Fill in placeholders
Replace these with your specific information:
- [TIME_PERIOD} - what month, year, week, or time period you want the calendar to be in
- [CALENDAR_IMPUT] - what you want to be in the calendar
- [what TIME_FOR_COMPLETION] - when you want everything done by, weekly, daily, times
- [FORMAT_LIKE_GOOGLE_SHEETS]- what you want the calendar to be presented in
- [EXCLUDED_DAYS] days you don't want anything in
- [STYLE] - what you want the calendar to look like

